{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 12 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:1",
      "text": "When he, too, had undergone blessed martyrdom, and died in the caldron into which he had been thrown, the seventh, the youngest of all, came forward:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:2",
      "text": "whom the tyrant pitying, though he had been dreadfully reproached by his brethren,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:3",
      "text": "seeing him already encompassed with chains, had him brought nearer, and endeavoured to counsel him, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:4",
      "text": "Thou seest the end of the madness of thy brethren: for they have died in torture through disobedience; and you, if disobedient, having been miserably tormented, will yourself perish prematurely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:5",
      "text": "But if you obey, you shall be my friend, and have a charge over the affairs of the kingdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:6",
      "text": "And having thus exhorted him, he sent for the mother of the boy; that, by condoling with her for the loss of so many sons, he might incline her, through the hope of safety, to render the survivor obedient.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:7",
      "text": "And he, after his mother had urged him on in the Hebrew tongue, (as we shall soon relate) says,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:8",
      "text": "Release me, that I may speak to the king and all his friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:9",
      "text": "And they, rejoicing exceedingly at the promise of the youth, quickly let him go.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:10",
      "text": "And he, running up to the pans, said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:11",
      "text": "Impious tyrant, and most blasphemous man, wert thou not ashamed, having received prosperity and a kingdom from God, to slay His servants, and to rack the doers of godliness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:12",
      "text": "Wherefore the divine vengeance is reserving thee for eternal fire and torments, which shall cling to thee for all time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:13",
      "text": "Wert thou not ashamed, man as thou art, yet most savage, to cut out the tongues of men of like feeling and origin, and having thus abused to torture them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:14",
      "text": "But they, bravely dying, fulfilled their religion towards God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:15",
      "text": "But thou shalt groan according to thy deserts for having slain without cause the champions of virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:16",
      "text": "Wherefore, he continued, I myself, being about to die,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:17",
      "text": "will not forsake the testimony of my brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:18",
      "text": "And I call upon the God of my fathers to be merciful to my race.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:19",
      "text": "But thee, both living and dead, he will punish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:fourth-maccabees.12.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 12:20",
      "text": "Thus having prayed, he hurled himself into the pans; and so expired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
